I have implemented support for google maps For the maps its very easy to apply a default style from <https://snazzymaps.com>. We can drop in a default one that will be applied unless an override is supplied with the data. The markers on the map are customizable via a supplied transparent png (tried animated gif, did NOT animate), the markers will require the lat and lng for the location they are marking, so these will need to be resolved when the data is saved. getting the geo codes isnt that hard using maps api. unclear exactly what data will be needing to be geo coded. If we want the map to show an area larger than just the encompassing section of the markers that adds more complexity. Like if we wanted to say the map shows USA and the markers on the map are all over, thats a bit more difficult than saying just show the map zoomed to the bounds of the markers. The api asks for a lat and lng for the center of the map, or can fit the bounds. Not sure the direction we need there but will need to explore that I think.
